{"id":471716,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mother_(Gorky_Novel)","text":"=\"preserve\">\"Mother\" (') is a novel written by Maxim Gorky in 1906. It is about an uneducated woman who began to take on extreme political beliefs. It was translated into many languages, many movies are also inspired by it.\nThe play \"The Mother\" by German playwright Bertolt Brecht is based on this novel.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Novel","surface_form":"novel","offset":30},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"written","offset":36},{"uri":"Maxim_Gorky","surface_form":"Maxim Gorky","offset":47},{"uri":"1906","surface_form":"1906","offset":62},{"uri":"Uneducated","surface_form":"uneducated","offset":83},{"uri":"Extreme","surface_form":"extreme","offset":121},{"uri":"Political","surface_form":"political","offset":129},{"uri":"Translation","surface_form":"translated","offset":155},{"uri":"Language","surface_form":"language","offset":176},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":192},{"uri":"German_people","surface_form":"German","offset":249},{"uri":"Playwright","surface_form":"playwright","offset":256},{"uri":"Bertolt_Brecht","surface_form":"Bertolt Brecht","offset":267}]}